time is coming far too frequently. During a recent performance of
``Death of a Salesman,'' its star, Brian Dennehy, was startled to
hear a cell phone ring near the end of the second act. Even more
disturbing was to hear the phone's being answered, and a woman in
the audience clearly saying, ``It's almost finished,'' and going on
to make dinner plans. Kevin Cahoon took a aggressive approach to a
recent cell-phone intrusion. When a phone rang during his
performance earlier this month as the transsexual rock singer in
``Hedwig and the Angry Inch'' at the Jane Street Theater, his
concentration broke, but his aplomb didn't. Cahoon marched off the
stage, pink fringe fluttering on his denim dress, took the phone
out of an audience member's hand and answered it. By Elaine Louie.
