<P>
   TURNER-SOUTH _ Today the TV empire that Ted built is launching
yet another cable network: Turner South. This regional network will
include a country music show from Nashville, a TV edition of
Southern Living magazine ( a Time Warner property), a comedy
program featuring an Atlanta-based comedy troupe, and World Classic
Wrestling re-runs packaged as ``classics.'' The real hook here is
the sports programming which will include Braves, Hawks and
Thrashers games that will help Turner/ Time Warner compete for
advertising and eyeballs with their nemeses over at Fox. The
network will be available in Georgia, Mississippi, Tennessee, South
Carolina and parts of North Carolina. We talk to the people behind
Turner South (including outgoing wunderkind Bill Burke) to find out
why they expects this new venture to be a hit. (Harris, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 35.
</P>
