<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   GUN-CONTROL (San Francisco) _ Gun control advocates are
applauding the nation's first appellate-level court ruling to
declare that gun manufacturers can be held accountable in criminal
shootings.
</P>
<P>
   WILLIE-BROWN (San Francisco _ San Francisco Mayor Willie Brown,
who four years ago expressed doubt about whether he could afford
life on a City Hall salary, received $780,000 in personal income
since taking office, his tax returns show. The mayor gave The San
Francisco Examiner one hour to review four years of federal income
tax returns dating back to 1995. No copies allowed. By CHUCK FINNIE
and ERIN McCORMICK.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNATIONAL NEWS (``i'' category)
</P>
<P>
   HAITI-AID (Port-au-Prince, Haiti) _ For decades, foreign
governments, aid agencies and lenders like the World Bank have
poured billions of dollars into Haiti. And for decades, those
efforts have come up pitifully short. Rather than push this nation
of 8 million toward prosperity, many aid workers, academics and
ordinary Haitians say, the aid has served merely to soothe foreign
consciences. While softening the social and political impact of
Haiti's destitution, it has converted many people here into charity
cases. By DUDLEY ALTHAUS. (For release Sunday, Oct. 3. Photos
available on NYT database)
</P>
<P>
   HAITI-COFFEE (Cap Rouge, Haiti) _ Aid planners bankrolled by the
U.S. government are betting that helping Orguste Boniface and his
neighbors sell their best coffee directly to American buyers will
put more cash in the farmers' pockets. In doing so, the cash may
give this stricken country its best, perhaps last, shot at staying
afloat. By DUDLEY ALTHAUS. (For release Sunday, Oct. 3. Graphic
available on NYT database.)
</P>
<P>
   BUSINESS/FINANCIAL NEWS (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CHEVRON (San Francisco) _ Wall Street is applauding Kenneth T.
Derr's 11-year tenure as chairman of the board and CEO of San
Francisco-based Chevron Corp. and has high regard for David
O'Reilly, who succeeds him at year's end. By GEORGE RAINE.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT (``e'' category)
</P>
<P>
   TV-McNASTY (Undated) _ Unless you're male, 21 or younger,
wearing a baseball cap, listening to hip-hop while simultaneously
playing Sega Dreamcast and _ here's the key _ fully, ragingly,
perpetually aroused, then there's no need for you to read any
further. Then again, you may get some joy out of an attempt to
artfully, maybe even intelligently, dissect ``Shasta McNasty,'' the
new UPN offering. by TIM GOODMAN.
</P>
<P>
   TV-GARDENING (Undated) _ Rebecca Kolls is a guru for the garden
set. She's fun, energetic and especially practical. That
combination is like honey to fans of ``Rebecca's Garden,'' her show
on the Home &AMP; Garden cable TV network. By DIANA RATHBONE.
</P>
