</P>
<P>
   KITCHEN-CLASSROOM (Albany, N.Y.) _ Johnny doesn't get it when it
comes to fractions and Susie needs to practice reading. Don't send
them to their rooms, send them to the kitchen. Cooking uses many of
the skills children struggle to learn and it can be a fun way to
reinforce those lessons. By RUTH FANTASIA.
