</P>
<P>
   BBN--CANDLESTICK (San Francisco) _ The honored guest missed the
start of its own farewell party. For the last night of baseball at
Candlestick, an impostor stepped in to play the role of the old
ballyard. Everyone spotted the fake right away. ``I'm so
disappointed that it's not windy and cold,'' said Eileen Regan, who
came down with a group from the Napa Valley. By GWEN KNAPP.
</P>
