A1913 &Cx1f; ttj-z
r d BC-KITCHEN-CLASSROOM-HNS     09-30 0331
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KITCHEN-CLASSROOM-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
KITCHEN CAN DOUBLE AS CLASSROOM FOR KIDS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By RUTH FANTASIA  
 c.1999 Albany Times Union  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALBANY, N.Y. _ Johnny doesn't get it when it comes to fractions
and Susie needs to practice reading. Don't send them to their
rooms, send them to the kitchen.
</P>
<P>
   Cooking uses many of the skills children struggle to learn and
it can be a fun way to reinforce those lessons.
</P>
<P>
   Ask Susie to read instructions off a box or read the recipe for
pizza aloud. As she does, ask her to gather the ingredients from
the cupboards. (She'll need to read the labels carefully to select
the correct ingredients).
</P>
<P>
   Let Johnny learn fractions by making a pizza and cutting it in
half, thirds, quarters, eighths, whatever. Take pieces away to
subtract fractions, put them back to add fractions _ all the while
having Johnny write the corresponding math problems. Eat the pizza.
</P>
<P>
   It's important to remember not to make cooking as big a struggle
as schoolwork. Keep the activities fun by remembering:
</P>
<P>
   _ To start early. Cooking with children always takes at least
twice as long as if you made the meal by yourself.
</P>
<P>
   _ Not to fret over spills and drips. Children are trying very
much to please you; don't ruin the lesson by being a clean freak
and trying to make them clean and cook at the same time. Everyone
can help clean up after the meal.
</P>
<P>
   _ Failure is learning, too. If a recipe flops, it may be because
they didn't follow the directions correctly.
</P>
<P>
   From a safety standpoint, make sure children aren't wearing
long, loose sleeves or dangling jewelry while cooking. Teach them
to wash their hands properly and handle food safely while cooking.
Keep knives sharp (dull knives are more likely to slip and cause
injuries) and resist the urge to use towels instead of pot holders,
as the towels can be cumbersome and catch on fire.
</P>
<P>
   And no matter how the dish turns out, try to eat it with a
smile.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-30-99 1230EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
