   FED-RATES (Washington) _ The economy is still roaring along, but
analysts say the Federal Reserve is likely to leave interest rates
alone at its policy meeting on Tuesday. But the outlook for coming
months is murkier, and the markets may look for hints when
Greenspan, the Fed chairman, speaks tonight in Minnesota. By
Richard W. Stevenson.
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ Looking at how the market ends the third
quarter. IN late morning trading, stocks were modestly higher. The
Dow Jones industrial average was up 0.56 percent, the S&AMP;P 500 up
0.68 percent and the Nasdaq composite index up 0.60 percent. The
30-year bond was yielding 6.09 percent. By Kenneth N. Gilpin.
