   FLOODS-PETS _ RALEIGH _ More than 1,000 dogs and cats were
rescued from floodwaters last week. Those sick and whose owners
could not be located were sent to NC State University's veterinary
school. While the vets are nursing them back to health in a field
hospital behind the NC Museum of Art, the Humane Society has taken
digital photos of every animal admitted to the hopsital and posted
them on a website this week for owners to look for their pets.
(Burritt, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
