   TIMOR-OBSTACLES (Remexio, East Timor) -- For a natural disaster,
you just have to battle the elements to bring relief. But 10 days
into the peacekeeping effort in East Timor, two basic obstacles
still stand between victims of the crisis and the food, water, and
medicine they need: a dangerous military environment and a lack of
transportation. By Indira A.R. Lakshmanan. 1200 words.
