<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-STROKE-BOX01-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    How to recognize stroke symptoms
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ Call 911 immediately if any of these stroke
symptoms strikes suddenly, the American Heart Association urges.
</P>
<P>
   _ Weakness, numbness, tingling or difficulty controlling one
side of the body.
</P>
<P>
   _ Slurred, labored or gibberish speech, or difficulty
understanding words.
</P>
<P>
   _ Blurry or lost vision, especially in one eye.
</P>
<P>
   _ Severe headache with no apparent cause, often with vomiting
and loss of consciousness.
</P>
<P>
   _ A sudden fall or unexplained dizziness, unsteadiness or loss
of coordination.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
