<TEXT>
<P>
   ATTENTION ALL EDITORS:
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times Syndicate has just transmitted a oneshot
article from The New York Times Magazine about Charles Saatchi,
whose controversial art show, ``Sensation: Young British Artists
From the Saatchi Collection,'' opens at the Brooklyn Museum of Art
on Oct. 2.
</P>
<P>
   New York 's Mayor Rudolph Giuliani, after viewing the exhibition
catalog, said the work was ``sick stuff'' and threatened to cut off
all subsidies to the museum unless it cancelled the show.
</P>
<P>
   On Sept. 28, the museum filed a lawsuit in federal court
accusing Giuliani of violating the First Amendment by threatening
to cut off its funding. City officials announced that they too are
preparing for legal action.
</P>
<P>
   HEADLINE: ``Charles Saatchi: The Collector''
</P>
