is scheduled to open Sat., Oct. 2, at the Brooklyn Museum of Art.
 &HT;    New York 's Mayor Rudolph Giuliani, after viewing the exhibition
catalog, said the work was ``sick stuff'' and threatened to cut off
all subsidies to the museum unless it cancelled the show.
 &HT;    On Sept. 28, the museum filed a lawsuit in federal court
accusing Giuliani of violating the First Amendment by threatening
to cut off its funding. City officials announced that they too are
preparing for legal action.
 &HT;    When ``Sensation'' was unveiled two years ago at the Royal
Academy of Arts in London, visitors to the exhibition, who had
