<HEADLINE>
TEST YOUR LITERARY KNOWLEDGE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   This one's different. In each group of four characters, one does
not belong in the literary work in which all the others appear.
Find the person who is out of place, and also identify the work of
fiction. So with two points possible for each entry, there's a
maximum of 20 points. You pass with 12 points and earn an A with
15.
</P>
<P>
   1. (a) Myrtle Wilson; (b) Daisy Buchanan; (c) Nicole Warren; (d)
Jordan Baker.
</P>
<P>
   2. (a) John Brooke; (b) David Madison; (c) Joseph Bhaer; (d)
Laurie Laurence.
</P>
<P>
   3. (a) Joseph Sedley; (b) George Osborne; (c) Rawdon Crawley;
(d) Henry Esmond.
</P>
<P>
   4. (a) Ashley Wilkes; (b) Frank Kennedy; (c) Charles Hamilton;
(d) Quentin Compson.
</P>
<P>
   5. (a) Robert Jordan; (b) Bill Gorton; (c) Mike Campbell; (d)
Jake Barnes.
</P>
<P>
   6. (a) Rodolphe Boulanger; (b) Jean Valjean; (c) Leon Depuis;
(d) Theodore Roualt.
</P>
<P>
   7. (a) Emma Woodhouse; (b) Catherine de Bourgh; (c) Elizabeth
Bennet; (d) Charlotte Lucas.
</P>
<P>
   8. (a) The Mad Hatter; (b) The Infant Phenomenon; ((c) The White
Knight; (d) The Mock Turtle.
</P>
<P>
   9. (a) Joe Harper; (b) Muff Potter; (c) Tom Canty; (d)
Huckleberry Finn.
</P>
<P>
   10. (a) Rose of Sharon; (b) Casey; (c) Muley Graves; (d) Sweets
Ramirez.
</P>
<P>
   Quiz answers: 1. Nicole Warren (c) isn't in F. Scott
Fitzgerald's ``The Great Gatsby;'' 2. David Madison (b) isn't in
Louisa May Alcott's ``Little Women;'' 3. Henry Esmond (d) isn't in
William M. Thackeray's ``Vanity Fair;'' 4. Quentin Compson (d)
isn't in Margaret Mitchell's ``Gone With the Wind;'' 5. Robert
Jordan (a) isn't in Ernest Hemingway's ``A Farewell to Arms;'' 6.
Jean Valjean (b) isn't in Gustave Flaubert's ``Madame Bovary;'' 7.
Emma Woodhouse (a) isn't in Jane Austen's ``Pride and Prejudice;''
8. The Infant Phenomenon (b) isn't in Lewis Carroll's ``Alice in
Wonderland;'' 9. Tom Canty (c) isn't in Mark Twain's ``The
Adventures of Tom Sawyer;'' 10. Sweets Ramirez (d) isn't in John
Steinbeck's ``The Grapes of Wrath.''
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
