<P>
   w/CHINA-CHRONO _ BEIJING _ A chronology of important events.
(Kunstel/Albright, Cox News Service). 10.
</P>
<P>
   CHINESE _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Gang Yu, Buming Bian and Ping Chen
rallied their fellow students to protest on three U.S. campuses
when the Chinese government cracked down on student protestors in
Tiananmen Square. But 10 years later, on the 50th anniversary of
the People's Republic of China, the three have a more positive view
of China's government and its future. To them, Chinese today have
food, better housing and a plethora of Western goods: They went
from shortage to surplus. A look at the first 50 years of the
People's Republic from the view of three Chinese citizens living
and working in Austin, Texas. (Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   OLYMPICS-IOC _ ATHENS, Greece _ The International Olympic
Committee executive board meets in the host city for the 2004 Games
amid fresh allegations that Atlanta Olympic bidding officials may
have been less pure than they claimed in their campaign for the
1996 Games. Ironically, Athens, one of Atlanta's rivals, has been
assumed over the years to have been the dirtiest contestant for the
1996 Games. (Roughton, Cox News Service). 30.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (i) International ad (s) Sports categories.
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-QUAKE _ MEXICO CITY _ A strong earthquake measuring about
7.4 rocked southern Mexico about 12:30 p.m. EDT Thursday, causing
buildings to sway in the capital for several minutes. While there
were no immediate reports of damage or injuries in the capital,
sporadic reports of damage from cities south have started trickling
in. Developing. (Ferriss, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Expected to move by 6:30 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-FOODAID _ WASHINGTON _ Experts warned Congress Thursday
that sending food aid to Russia has fed corruption and aided U.S.
farmers but does not help the Russian people. The warning came as
Russian officials announced that they are seeking more food
assistance this year. The U.S. Department of Agriculture has the
request under consideration. (Malone, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Expected to move by 6:30 p.m. EDT.
</P>
