<P>
   BRADLEY-MONEY (Washington) _ Democratic presidential hopeful
Bill Bradley raised more money than Vice President Al Gore in the
third quarter of the year and ended the period with more money in
the bank than the vice president, furthering the impression that
Gore's candidacy is in trouble. Meanwhile among Republicans, Texas
Gov. George W. Bush reported donations of $56 million for the year
so far, astronomically ahead of his nearest competitor. By BENNETT
ROTH.
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-BOOK (Houston) _ Republican presidential hopeful George W.
Bush has removed Mickey Herskowitz, a sports columnist for the
Houston Chronicle, as the ghostwriter of the Texas governor's
autobiography in a dispute over how many policy details the book
should contain. By WENDY BENJAMINSON. (Already filed.)
</P>
