   &QL; 
 &UR; LIES &LR;  _ Resume fibbing has been around since, well, resumes. After
Adam was expelled from the garden for biting into the apple, an old
business joke goes, he put down ``quality control supervisor, Eden
Produce'' on his resume. Laughter abruptly stops, however, when
seemingly innocuous fibbing turns into gross exaggeration or
out-and-out lying. Often, the results are far from harmless for the
employee, who loses his job and reputation, and the company, which
bears the cost of replacing the employee and might lose prestige.
By Sam McManis
</P>
<P>
   &UR; LIESBOX _  &LR; Tips for reference-checkers. By Sam McManis
</P>
