   &UR; FLYCAST &LR;  _ For the third time in two weeks, CMGI Inc. of
Andover, Mass., has snapped up a Bay Area business in its
aggressive bid to dominate the Internet advertising sector. Flycast
Communications Corp., a San Francisco company that sells
advertising space on small and midsize Web sites, was yesterday's
target. CMGI is paying about $741 million in stock for Flycast. By
Carol Emert
</P>
