<P>
   (NYT4) PORT-AU-PRINCE, Haiti -- Sept. 30, 1999 --
HAITI-AID-1-HNS, 09-30 -- A Haitian youngster frolics in a
garbage-choked drainage gully that runs through the Port-au-Prince
neighborhood of Cite Absalon. The U.S. government has been spending
about $100 million a year in Haiti since 1994. ``They're spending a
lot of money, but things are getting worse,'' says Michelle Carter,
an official in Port-au-Prince with CARE, a U.S-funded aid agency
that has been working in Haiti since 1959. ``It seems like the
needs have increased and people's expectations have increased.''
(Andrew Innerarity/Houston Chronicle Photo)
