The one-man show, about a performance artist who kidnaps a
conservative senator's dog, begins previews on Friday night. ``When
I read it, I knew it was something I wanted to do,'' says
Linn-Baker, who is also one of the play's producers. ``I was just
praying I wasn't the only one that thought that.'' (Sara
Krulwich/New York Times Photo)
</P>
