<HEADLINE>
OUTTAKES FROM BEATTY'S NEWEST GIG
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l` lifestyles file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   A spy who was at  &UR; Warren Beatty &LR; 's maybe-I-am maybe-I'm-not
announcement Wednesday night whispers:
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Lara Flynn Boyle &LR; , 29, and  &UR; Jack Nicholson &LR; , 52, were looking
``very affectionate'' at the table right in front of podium.
 &UR; Courtney Love &LR; , dressed in her trademark ``appropriately smutty''
fashion, kept stepping outside to smoke.
</P>
<P>
   Despite its political nature, the event began like a Hollywood
gala, with taped clips of celebrities wishing Beatty well. The
cheerleaders included  &UR; Barbra Streisand &LR; ,  &UR; Dustin Hoffman &LR; ,  &UR; John &LR; 
 &UR; Burton  &LR; and  &UR; Willie Brown &LR; , whose segment was booed.
</P>
<P>
   By the end of the evening Beatty ``seemed like a character'' in
one of his movies, overwhelmed and a bit befuddled.
</P>
<P>
   When his wife,  &UR; Annette Bening &LR; , was asked whether taking part
in politics was anything like appearing in a political movie, such
as ``The American President,'' she gave a definite ``No. This is
real life.''
</P>
<P>
   P.S. Real life?  &UR; Arnold Schwarzenegger  &LR; says in an interview in
the November issue of Talk that he's thinking about running for
governor of California in 2002. ``The possibility is there,'' he
said, ``because I feel it inside. I feel there are a lot of people
standing still and not doing enough. And there's a vacuum.''
</P>
<P>
   As to his past life, Schwarzenegger said he would come clean.
``What it is is what it is. I inhaled, exhaled. Everything.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ Upon reading in New York magazine that  &UR; Kevin Costner &LR; 's
frontal nude scenes in ``For Love of the Game'' were cut, said one
Universal official, partly because a test screening audience
``giggled at Kevin's penis,'' reader  &UR; Tom Costner &LR;  comments:
``Clearly Kev comes from the other branch of the Costner family
tree, the phallically challenged one.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Matt Damon &LR;  and  &UR; Ben Affleck &LR;  are turning  &UR; Howard Zinn &LR; 's
book ``A People's History of the United States'' into a movie. Zinn
is a counterculture intellectual famous in the '60s and '70s, and
was mentor to Damon (who quoted him in ``Good Will Hunting''). He
was also mentor to  &UR; Alice Walker &LR;  and  &UR; Marion Wright &LR; 
 &UR; Edelman &LR; , early friend of the Clintons and founder of the
Children's Defense Fund.
</P>
<P>
   Zinn will speak about his book at the San Francisco Book
Festival at Fort Mason on October 16; he'll be introduced by
Edelman, who's speaking just before him on her memoir, `Lanterns: A
Memoir of Mentors.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Noting how neat it is that one can dial POPCORN for the time,
 &UR; Ted Herzberg  &LR; would like some help with a device by which to
remember the new weather service number for San Francisco: (831)
656-1725. It's not easy, because a 1 is a 1 is a 1. Any ideas?
