   &UR; COMMERCIALS &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ A new TV ad for Dannon yogurt features celebrity volleyball
player  &UR; Gabrielle Reece &LR; , and includes a picture of Reece as a
girl, sitting next to a table on which is a carton of Dannon
yogurt. The ad's line: ``You grew up eating Dannon.''
</P>
<P>
   But the picture is fake. Its original version, without yogurt,
appears in Reece's book, ``Big Girl in the Middle.''
</P>
<P>
   An ad executive told Advertising Age that the ad wasn't intended
to fool anyone; it was intended to be ironic, ``underscoring the
sardonic tone of the campaign,'' says the magazine.
</P>
<P>
   _ New York cabdrivers are unhappy about a new campaign for the
clothing company French Connection U.K., which features the
company's initials in ads atop the taxis. ``It's clearly
denigrating to the industry,'' said New York Taxi Commissioner
 &UR; Allan Fromberg &LR; .
